title: China Lucks Out Again as Out-of-Control Rocket Booster Falls in the Pacific
description: For the fourth time, the country’s space program used a 23-ton launcher that made an uncontrolled re-entry back to Earth, prompting nervous sky-watching and airspace closures in Europe.
dc:creator: Kenneth Chang
media:description: A Long March 5B rocket lifting off from China’s satellite launch center in Hainan Province on Monday, in an image released by state media.
